# React Maintenance

- Centralize repeated third-party setup in `src/components/common/` instead of
  re-registering modules in feature components.
- Avoid one-line feature re-export files unless they document a real feature
  boundary or add behavior.
- Prefer canonical constants for resume/profile facts; do not duplicate titles,
  locations, schools, or other stable facts in components.
- Give custom clickable elements and icon-only controls accessible names with
  `aria-label` or visible text.
- Keep render-time objects and lookups stable when they are reused in maps or
  memoized children. For example, hoist sentinel objects and use `Set` for
  repeated membership checks.
- When cleaning redundancy, favor small shared helpers that match existing
  patterns over broad rewrites.
